<TITLE> Rotary to give backpacks to poor rural students </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 30 (bdnews24.com)- Rotary International of Bangladesh is to distribute school bags worth $50,000 among poor students in rural areas. District governor Rafique Ahmed Siddique made the disclosure at a press conference at the Jatiya Press Club on the occasion of the inauguration of Rotary year 2007-08, organised by Rotary International Bangladesh. At the press conference, Rafique Ahmed said that it would spend $50,000 at the initial stage on a" backpack" programme for school students in rural areas of Bangladesh. Each backpack would include a waterproof bag, an umbrella, a dictionary, rubber and pencil. Besides the backpack programme, Rotary would spend 1,50,000 dollars this year on arsenic mitigation. Most of the money would be spent for digging arsenic-free wells. bdnews
